headline.print_headline: Libyan Al Qaeda Suspect Seeks to Toss Statements in U.S. Case
headline.main: Libyan Al Qaeda Suspect Seeks to Toss Statements in U.S. Case

lead_paragraph: Suspected al Qaeda figure Abu Anas al-Liby told a U.S. judge on Wednesday that statements he made to U.S. interrogators should not be allowed at trial because he felt he had no choice but to talk.
